You are a senior Python software architect.

Build a production-quality local web application using:

- Python 3.14.3
- Flask
- SQLite
- Jinja2 templates
- Bootstrap 5 (CDN)
- Chart.js (CDN)

The purpose of the app is to monitor and record the Maximum Sustainable Fortnightly Income (MSFI) from a superannuation portfolio.

The system must be:

- Simple
- Cleanly structured
- Maintainable
- Modular
- Fully commented
- Suitable for a single-user local installation
- No authentication required
- No external APIs

--------------------------------------------------
PROJECT REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------

The app must:

1. Allow monthly entry of:
   - Snapshot date
   - Total portfolio value
   - Value of:
        - Growth
        - Balanced
        - Conservative
        - Cash
   - 5-year return rates for each option
   - Actual fortnightly income being withdrawn
   - Optional notes

2. Automatically calculate:
   - Portfolio weightings
   - Weighted expected annual return
   - Expected annual earnings
   - Maximum sustainable annual income
   - Maximum sustainable fortnightly income
   - 10% safety buffer MSFI
   - 20% safety buffer MSFI
   - Income risk flag if actual withdrawal exceeds MSFI

3. Store all monthly snapshots in SQLite.

4. Provide:
   - Dashboard view (latest snapshot summary)
   - Historical table view
   - Chart showing:
        - Portfolio value over time
        - Sustainable fortnightly income over time
        - Actual fortnightly income over time

