ENGINEERING RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Use application factory pattern.
- Separate calculation logic into calculations.py.
- All financial math must be pure functions.
- Round monetary outputs to 2 decimal places.
- Use SQLite file database named msfi.db.
- Use parameterized SQL queries (no ORM).
- Use Bootstrap for layout.
- Use Chart.js for charts.
- Include inline comments explaining calculations.
- Include a README section at the bottom explaining how to run.

--------------------------------------------------
CALCULATION SPECIFICATION
--------------------------------------------------

Weighted Return = sum(weight_i × return_i)

Where:

weight_i = option_value / total_value

Annual Earnings = total_value × weighted_return

Maximum Sustainable Annual Income = Annual Earnings

Maximum Sustainable Fortnightly Income = Annual Earnings / 26

10% Buffer MSFI = MSFI × 0.90

20% Buffer MSFI = MSFI × 0.80

Risk Flag:
    If actual_fortnightly_income > MSFI → "Overdrawing"
    Else if actual_fortnightly_income > 10% buffer → "Caution"
    Else → "Safe"

